{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ATC7jxfbN6vF9tX2MbMJb7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is stable: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-2`) and 2 SECONDARY members, all pods Ready.\n\n**What was wrong and what I changed:**\n\n| Probe | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Readiness `timeoutSeconds` | `1` | `5` |\n| Readiness `initialDelaySeconds` | `5` | `30` |\n| Readiness `failureThreshold` | `2` | `6` |\n| Readiness eval | `db.hello()` RS-state check | `db.adminCommand(\"ping\")` |\n| Liveness `timeoutSeconds` | `1` | `5` |\n| Liveness `initialDelaySeconds` | `15` | `60` |\n| Liveness `failureThreshold` | `2` | `6` |\n\nThe critical fixes:\n1. **`timeoutSeconds: 1`** — authenticated `mongosh` routinely takes >1s, causing constant false failures.\n2. **`failureThreshold: 2` on liveness** — pods were killed after just 2 slow probe responses, cycling the whole set.\n3. **Readiness RS-state check** (`isWritablePrimary || secondary`) — a pod in STARTUP/RECOVERING state fails this, which with `OrderedReady` prevents pod-1 from ever starting since pod-0 can't form a quorum alone. Replaced with a plain `ping`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":265,"cache_read_input_tokens":37969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":265},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fcd293ca-caab-46a1-8bb8-3ec0efc6d57d","uuid":"684e7a7c-6616-4a1d-8268-1ce86f5a13d0","request_id":"req_011Ccg9yNRhsTyXQH4yuJUHr"}
